The paper deals with Multi-Object Tracking (MOT) algorithms, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new algorithm that uses machine learning techniques to model dependencies among tracklets, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses the structural support vector machine algorithm (SSVM) to learn the weights of hyperedges, which could place it in the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
